2 unit Belgian Waffle
½ ounce Cashews
4 teaspoon Honey
¼ cup Shredded Coconut
¾ cup Yogurt
4 tablespoon Crème Fraîche
3 ounce Berry Compote
Salt

• Toast waffles until golden. Drop honey (in packet) in a small bowl of
warm water to soften. Roughly chop cashews.

• Heat a medium dry pan over medium-high heat. Add cashews and
coconut; cook, stirring frequently, until lightly browned and fragrant,
2-4 minutes. (TIP: Keep a close eye on pan to avoid burning.) Transfer to
a plate.

• Once waffles are toasted, cut into ¼-inch pieces.

• In a second small bowl (medium bowl for 4 servings), whisk together
yogurt, crème fraîche, honey, and a pinch of salt until well combined.

• If using jars, divide half the honey yogurt between jars. Top with half
the berry compote, half the toasted cashews and coconut, and half
the waffle pieces. Repeat to make a second layer. If using bowls, divide
honey yogurt between bowls. Top with berry compote and toasted
cashews and coconut. Place waffle pieces in the center. Serve.